<style>
    .scroll {
        overflow-y: scroll;
        height: 130px;
        width: 300px;
        background-color: #fff;
        margin: 0 0 10px 0;
    }

        .scroll::-webkit-scrollbar {
            width: 5px;
        }

        .scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
            -webkit-box-shadow: inset 0 0 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .scroll::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
            border-radius: 5px;
            -webkit-box-shadow: inset 0 0 6px red;
        }
</style>

<body>
    <div class="scroll">
        We often use the !important property in CSS to ignore rules or styles
        applied to an element and instead apply rules that has !important property.
        You can further override the !important rules using ...
    </div>
</body>